com.nimsoft.nimbus
Class NimCallback

java.lang.Object
  com.nimsoft.nimbus.NimCallback

public class NimCallback
extends Object

This class is used as a container for all callback methods in a NimSessionListener. It should not be used directly (see NimProbe.registerCallback(java.lang.Object, java.lang.String, java.lang.String) and NimSessionListener.registerCallback(java.lang.Object, java.lang.String, java.lang.String) for callback registration).

Add a callback (with NimSession as first parameter) without any int or String parameters. If the callback method contains a PDS parameter, the data PDS will be passed as this parameter.

Parameters:
object - The object that has the method to be called
cmd - the command name
methodname - the method to be called. This method must exist for the given object (introspection will be used to determine whether a method with a matching name and parameter list can be found).

Add a callback (with NimSession as first para) with int and String parameters. The parameternames are converted to the type given in the method (String and int parameters are legal). If the callback method contains a PDS parameter, the data PDS is returned in this parameter.

protected void addNoSession(Object object,
                            String cmd,
                            String methodname,

                     throws NimException
Add a callback (no NimSession at the start) with no parameters. The parameternames are converted to the type given in the method (String and int parameters are legal). If the callback method contains a PDS parameter, the data PDS is returned in this parameter.

Parameters:
object - The object that has the method to be called
cmd - The command name in the PDS header
methodname - The methodname to be called
inseparatethread - True if started in separate thread
